NOTE: for the ViRGE/VX,DX,GX,GX2 chipsets you need XFree86 3.3.1 or newer.
You should use the XF86_SVGA server.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

26. Appendix B. Supported PCMCIA cards

These cards are supported by David Hinds' PCMCIA package and this list is
taken from his web page ([http://pcmcia-cs.sourceforge.net/] here).

CardBus cards are listed at the end of each section. At this time, all
CardBus drivers should be treated as experimental. Beware that some cards
have 16-bit and CardBus versions with very similar names. If the CardBus
version is not specifically listed as supported here, then you should not
expect it to work.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

26.1. Ethernet cards

  * SMC, Megahertz and Ositech cards use the smc91c92_cs driver
   
  * 3Com and Farallon cards use the 3c589_cs driver
   
  * Fujitsu, TDK, RATOC, CONTEC, Eagle and Nextcom cards use the fmvj18x_cs
    driver
   

All other cards use the pcnet_cs driver. Other NE2000-compatible cards that
are not on the list are also likely to work with pcnet_cs.

  * 3Com 3c589, 3c589B, 3c589C, 3c589D (3c589_cs)
   
  * 3Com Megahertz 3CCE589E, 3CXE589D, 3CXE589EC (3c589_cs)
   
